.TH babychess "6" "@DATE@" "babychess @VERSION_NUMBER@" "Games"
.SH NAME
babychess \- a GUI chess application
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbabychess\fP
.br
\fBbabychess\fP --play
.br
\fBbabychess\fP --internet
.br
\fBbabychess\fP --edit-game-archive [\fIPGN-FILE\fR]
.br
\fBbabychess\fP --edit-game [\fIPGN-FILE\fR]
.br
\fBbabychess\fP --edit-position [\fIFEN-FILE\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
BabyChess is a graphical chess application.  It can be used to play games
against chess engines, play chess on the internet, and edit PGN and FEN files.
It also includes it's own chess engine. 
.TP
\fBbabychess\fP
Open the start window giving access to all functionality.
.TP
\fBbabychess\fP --play
Play a local game of chess.  Players can be humans or chess engines running on
the local computer.
.TP
\fBbabychess\fP --internet
Play chess on the internet.  BabyChess will prompt for the name and port of an
internet chess server, and for a username and password.  Once logged in, games
can be played against other human players.
.TP
\fBbabychess\fP --edit-game-archive [\fIPGN-FILE\fR]
Open a PGN file for viewing or editing.  The PGN file may contain any number of
chess games.  If the filename is omitted, open a new chess game archive
containing zero games.
.TP
\fBbabychess\fP --edit-game [\fIPGN-FILE\fR]
Open a PGN file that contains exactly one game for viewing and editing.  If
the filename is omitted, open a new game from the standard starting position. 
.TP
\fBbabychess\fP --edit-position [\fIFEN-FILE\fR]
Open a FEN file containing exactly one position for viewing and editing.  If
the filename is omitted, edit the standard starting position.

.SH AUTHOR
\fBBabyChess\fP was conceived and developed by Jerome KUNEGIS.
